Something about the Toast Machine

About:
Toast Machine idea is a software to turn a ubuntu box into a self-service distributor of free software by burning ISOs on
CD/DVD and letting the guest insert his usb portable storage media and copy free software (zip/dmg) on it. For example during a Linux Day you can prepare a Toast Machine (with an old PC capable of burn without freezing) with ISO images and zip/dmg files so guests can view what the Toast Machine offers and take home free software, maybe donating something simbolic to the LUG to pay the blank CD/DVD used.

Runtime dependencies:
 - brasero
 - python-gksu2
 - udisks
 - python-pam

Issues:
 - On Ubuntu the user who runs toast-machine must belong to 'disk' group

